docs.abstract: Mr. Mulvaney, a central figure in the president’s pressure campaign on Ukraine, defied a subpoena to testify in the House impeachment inquiry and was never called by the Senate.
docs.snippet: Mr. Mulvaney, a central figure in the president’s pressure campaign on Ukraine, defied a subpoena to testify in the House impeachment inquiry and was never called by the Senate.
docs.lead_paragraph: WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. — President Trump on Friday pushed out Mick Mulvaney, his acting White House chief of staff, and replaced him with Representative Mark Meadows, a stalwart conservative ally, shaking up his team in the middle of one of the biggest crises of his presidency.

headline.main: Trump Names Mark Meadows Chief of Staff, Ousting Mick Mulvaney
headline.print_headline: Mulvaney Ousted As Chief of Staff

docs.abstract: The court will soon hear arguments in its first major abortion case since the retirement of Justice Anthony M. Kennedy. It could leave Louisiana with a single abortion clinic.
docs.snippet: The court will soon hear arguments in its first major abortion case since the retirement of Justice Anthony M. Kennedy. It could leave Louisiana with a single abortion clinic.
docs.lead_paragraph: SHREVEPORT, La. — Kathaleen Pittman, the director of the Hope Medical Group for Women, remembers when there were 11 abortion clinics in Louisiana. Now there are only three, hers among them. Soon, depending on how the Supreme Court rules in a case to be argued on Wednesday, there may be just one, in New Orleans, more than 300 miles away.

headline.main: An Abortion Clinic’s Fate Before a Transformed Supreme Court
headline.print_headline: Distant Battle Line In an Abortion Struggle

docs.abstract: A president who is at his strongest politically when he has a human target to attack has found it harder to confront a growing outbreak that has rattled the country.
docs.snippet: A president who is at his strongest politically when he has a human target to attack has found it harder to confront a growing outbreak that has rattled the country.
docs.lead_paragraph: PALM BEACH, Fla. — Defending against criticism of his handling of the coronavirus, President Trump suggested the other day that he could hardly have been expected to be ready for such an unexpected crisis.

headline.main: For Trump, Coronavirus Proves to Be an Enemy He Can’t Tweet Away
headline.print_headline: Twitter Pulpit Is No Match For Viral Foe

docs.abstract: Emergency rooms across the country are preparing for a crush of cases, but with limited capacity and supplies, administrators fear they will not be ready.
docs.snippet: Emergency rooms across the country are preparing for a crush of cases, but with limited capacity and supplies, administrators fear they will not be ready.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — One Seattle-area hospital has already seen patient care delayed by the stringent infection-control practices that the government recommended for suspected coronavirus cases. Another in Chicago switched Thursday morning into “surge” mode, setting up triage tents in its ambulance bay and dedicating an entire floor to coronavirus patients. At least one is already receiving emergency supplies from the federal government’s stockpile.

headline.main: U.S. Hospitals Prepare for Coronavirus, With the Worst Still to Come
headline.print_headline: Hospitals Brace for Worst While Facing Limitations

headline.main: Trump Won’t Be Getting a Coronavirus Test, His Doctor Says

docs.abstract: The administration’s response to the coronavirus has repeatedly matched public health experts against a hesitant White House, where worry of panic dominates.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — After weeks of conflicting signals from the Trump administration about the coronavirus, the government’s top health officials decided late last month that when President Trump returned from a trip to India, they would tell him they had to be more blunt about the dangers of the outbreak.

headline.main: Inside Trump Administration, Debate Raged Over What to Tell Public
headline.print_headline: Behind Coronavirus Chaos at the White House
